Package: xt-ndpi-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 dkms,
 build-essential,
 linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-arm64 | linux-headers,
Description: nDPI xt_ndpi netfilter module (DKMS source)
 Out-of-tree netfilter kernel module providing the iptables/ip6tables
 "-m ndpi" match, built from the vel21ripn nDPI fork (carries the kernel
 6.8.x fixes). DKMS compiles xt_ndpi against the running kernel on install
 and automatically rebuilds it on every kernel upgrade, so the module keeps
 loading across reboots without manual intervention.
 .
 Using the "-m ndpi" match from iptables also requires the userspace
 xtables extension in the xt-ndpi-iptables package.

Package: xt-ndpi-iptables
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 xt-ndpi-dkms (= ${source:Version}),
 iptables,
Description: nDPI iptables extension (libxt_ndpi.so)
 Userspace xtables extension implementing the "-m ndpi" match for
 iptables/ip6tables, used to act on flows classified by nDPI (e.g.
 "-m ndpi --proto bittorrent -j DROP"). Built from the same nDPI revision as
 xt-ndpi-dkms so the protocol IDs stay in lockstep with the kernel module.
 Depends on xt-ndpi-dkms because the match is inert without the xt_ndpi
 kernel module loaded.
